log
@borrando viejos
@
text
@- Install:
	a) mkdir jrubik.
	b) Copy the jar file JRubik-bin-version.zip to folder jrubik.
		cp JRubik-bin-version.zip ./jrubik
	c) cd ./rubik
	d)unzip JRubik-bin-version.zip.
	e)Finally exec run.bat (java -Xms100m -Xmx500m -jar JRubik.jar)

Main changes:
- This JRubik version runs using JPF plugin framework http://sourceforge.net/projects/jpf 
- The folder resources had been moved to : ./data
- The catalogs (ej.FoodMart.xml) are located on the directory: ./data/resources/catalog
- Menus are located on : ./data/resources/mdxmenu
- Bookmark are located on : ./data/resources/mdxbookmark
- This version contains a Foodmart memory database version (smallFoodmart) 
	located on: ./data/resources/hsql/smallFoodmart.script
	the first query is very slow because is necessary to load the DB in memory.
- The plugins has been renamed:
chat_ComponentPlugin is now es.aeat.eett.rubik.chart
tableRubikPlugin is now es.aeat.eett.rubik.tableRubik

This changes on the plugin names could affect the previus defined menus and bookmarks by the user.
If you are interested into mantain you have to replace the plugin name on the bookmark or menu file. 
This files are located on the directories: ./data/resources/mdxmenu and ./data/resources/mdxbookmark

- How to Add a new jdbc driver:
	1- Copy the jar file to the folder ./plugins/es.aeat.eett.rubik.core/lib
	2- Edit file ./es.aeat.eett.rubik.core/plugin.xml
		the last lines are:
				<library id="hsqldb_1.8.02" path="lib/hsqldb.jar" type="code">		
				</library>		
				<library id="mysql-connector-java" path="lib/mysql-connector-java-3.1.7-bin.jar" type="code">		
				</library>
			</runtime>
		</plugin>		
		If the new driver is named "otherDriver.jar" create a new 
		 tag defining the library in this way:		 
				<library id="hsqldb_1.8.02" path="lib/hsqldb.jar" type="code">		
				</library>		
				<library id="mysql-connector-java" path="lib/mysql-connector-java-3.1.7-bin.jar" type="code">		
				</library>
				
				<library id="otherDriver.jar" path="lib/otherDriver.jar" type="code">		
				</library>
			</runtime>
		</plugin>		
	3) Update mondrian.properties the file:
		mondrian.jdbcDrivers=com.mysql.jdbc.Driver,org.hsqldb.jdbcDriver
		
		Finally save the file@


